#. Tag: title
#: apps_pidgin.xml:9
#, no-c-format
msgid "Pidgin: Instant Messaging"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: dm:translation
#: apps_pidgin.xml:13
#, no-c-format
msgid "yes"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_pidgin.xml:16
#, no-c-format
msgid "Pidgin is an instant messaging (IM) client that allows you to connect to multiple accounts simultaneously. Chat live with your contacts, regardless of which IM system they use."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_pidgin.xml:21
#, no-c-format
msgid "Pidgin supports the following instant messaging protocols: AIM, Bonjour, Gadu-Gadu, Google Talk, Groupwise, ICQ, IRC, SIMPLE, XMPP, and Zephyr. Microsoft Office Communicator is also supported if you install the additional package <package>pidgin-plugin-sipe</package> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_pidgin.xml:27
#, no-c-format
msgid "In the following, learn how to set up Pidgin and how to communicate with your contacts."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: apps_pidgin.xml:32
#, no-c-format
msgid "Starting Pidgin"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_pidgin.xml:34
#, no-c-format
msgid "To start Pidgin, open the Activities Overview by pressing <keycap function=\"meta\"/> and search for <literal>pid</literal> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: apps_pidgin.xml:40
#, no-c-format
msgid "Configuring Accounts"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_pidgin.xml:42
#, no-c-format
msgid "To use Pidgin, you must already have an account for the messaging service you want to use. For example, to use Pidgin to chat via AIM, you must first have an AIM account."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: apps_pidgin.xml:49
#, no-c-format
msgid "Adding and Editing Accounts in Pidgin"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_pidgin.xml:51
#, no-c-format
msgid "If you start Pidgin for the first time, a message appears, prompting you to configure an account. Proceed with <guimenu>Add</guimenu> to add a new account."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_pidgin.xml:56
#, no-c-format
msgid "If you have already configured an account and want to add a new one or modify existing ones, open this dialog via <menuchoice> <guimenu>Accounts</guimenu> <guimenu>Manage Accounts</guimenu> </menuchoice> . Either <guimenu>Add</guimenu> a new account, or <guimenu>Modify</guimenu> or <guimenu>Delete</guimenu> existing ones."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_pidgin.xml:66
#, no-c-format
msgid "The Add/Modify Account dialog opens. Use the <guimenu>Basic</guimenu> tab to select a protocol and enter or modify your login credentials."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_pidgin.xml:70
#, no-c-format
msgid "The availability of other tabs and the data you are required to enter depends on the protocol you have chosen. In most cases, server details such as address and port number need to be entered on the <guimenu>Advanced</guimenu> tab."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_pidgin.xml:76
#, no-c-format
msgid "On the <guimenu>Proxy</guimenu> tab you can enter a custom proxy configuration for the chosen protocol. By default the system settings ( <guimenu>Use Global Proxy Settings</guimenu> ) are preselected. This default should be sufficient for most users."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_pidgin.xml:84
#, no-c-format
msgid "Continue with <guimenu>Add</guimenu> or <guimenu>Save</guimenu> . Make sure all accounts you want to use are set to <guimenu>Enabled</guimenu> in the resulting <guimenu>Accounts</guimenu> window. If you want to temporarily disable an account, deselect it in the <guimenu>Enabled</guimenu> column."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: apps_pidgin.xml:95
#, no-c-format
msgid "Managing Contacts"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_pidgin.xml:97
#, no-c-format
msgid "Use the <guimenu>Contact List</guimenu> to manage your contacts (so-called <quote>Buddies</quote> ). You can add and remove contacts and organize them in groups, so they are easy to find."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: apps_pidgin.xml:104
#, no-c-format
msgid "Adding Contacts"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_pidgin.xml:106
#, no-c-format
msgid "To add a contact, click <menuchoice> <guimenu>Buddies</guimenu> <guimenu>Add Buddy</guimenu> </menuchoice> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_pidgin.xml:112
#, no-c-format
msgid "Select the <guimenu>Account</guimenu> for which you want to add a contact."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_pidgin.xml:117
#, no-c-format
msgid "Enter the contact's user name under <guimenu>Buddy' username</guimenu> . Ask your contact for this name prior to adding the contact&mdash;this data is required and usually depends on the protocol."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_pidgin.xml:124
#, no-c-format
msgid "By default the contact is shown under the name he has provided with his account. Use <guimenu>(Optional): Alias</guimenu> to display the contact with a custom name. With some protocols you can also send the contact an invite message with <guimenu>(Optional): Invite Message</guimenu> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_pidgin.xml:132
#, no-c-format
msgid "If you have sorted your contacts by group, choose an existing group from the drop-down text box or enter a new group name."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_pidgin.xml:138
#, no-c-format
msgid "Proceed with <guimenu>Add</guimenu> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_pidgin.xml:144
#, no-c-format
msgid "In case the groups or the newly added contacts are not displayed in the contact list, check the display preferences by clicking <menuchoice> <guimenu>Buddies</guimenu> <guimenu>Show</guimenu> </menuchoice> . Activate <guimenu>Offline Buddies</guimenu> and <guimenu>Empty Groups</guimenu> to make all contacts and groups appear in the <guimenu>Contact List</guimenu> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_pidgin.xml:153
#, no-c-format
msgid "To remove a contact from the list, right-click the name of that contact, select <guimenu>Remove</guimenu> and confirm your choice."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: apps_pidgin.xml:159
#, no-c-format
msgid "Chatting with Friends"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_pidgin.xml:161
#, no-c-format
msgid "To chat with other participants, you need to be connected to the Internet. After a successful login, you are usually marked as <guimenu>Available</guimenu> in the <guimenu>Contact List</guimenu> , and are visible to others. To change your status, click the drop-down box at the bottom of the <guimenu>Contact List</guimenu> and select another option."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_pidgin.xml:169
#, no-c-format
msgid "To open a chat session, double-click a contact name in the <guimenu>Contact List</guimenu> . The chat screen opens. Type your message, then press <keycap function=\"enter\"/> to send."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_pidgin.xml:175
#, no-c-format
msgid "If you open more than one chat session, the new session appears as a tab in the existing chat window. To see all messages of a session and to be able to write a reply, click the tab of that session. To see multiple session side by side, use the mouse to drag a tab out of the window. A second window will open."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_pidgin.xml:183
#, no-c-format
msgid "To close a chat session, close the tab or window for it."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: apps_pidgin.xml:188
#, no-c-format
msgid "Finding a Contact"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_pidgin.xml:189
#, no-c-format
msgid "In case you contact list is very long, contacts may be hard to find. Use <keycombo> <keycap function=\"control\"/> <keycap>F</keycap> </keycombo> to open a search box at the bottom of the contact list. Type one or more letters to find a contact. Use <keycap function=\"down\"/> to move to the next result, or <keycap function=\"up\"/> to move to the previous result."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: apps_pidgin.xml:200
#, no-c-format
msgid "For More Information"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_pidgin.xml:202
#, no-c-format
msgid "This chapter only explains the basic configuration and usage option of Pidgin. For more information, click <menuchoice> <guimenu>Help</guimenu> <guimenu>Online Help</guimenu> </menuchoice> to open the FAQs in a browser."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_pidgin.xml:207
#, no-c-format
msgid "For updates about new features and for the latest information, refer to the home page of the project at <link xlink:href=\"https://pidgin.im/\"/> ."
msgstr ""

